128 gentity_t *G_TestEntityPosition(gentity_t *ent)
129 {
130  trace_t tr;
131  int mask;
132 
133  if (ent->clipmask)
134  {
135  mask = ent->clipmask;
136  }
137  else
138  {
139  mask = MASK_SOLID;
140  }
141 
142  if (ent->client)
143  {
144  trap_TraceCapsule(&tr, ent->client->ps.origin, ent->r.mins, ent->r.maxs, ent->client->ps.origin, ent->s.number, mask);
145 
146  if (!tr.startsolid && (ent->client->ps.eFlags & EF_PRONE))
147  {
148  vec3_t org, flatforward, point;
149 
150  AngleVectors(ent->client->ps.viewangles, flatforward, NULL, NULL);
151  flatforward[2] = 0;
152  VectorNormalizeFast(flatforward);
153 
154  org[0] = ent->client->ps.origin[0] + flatforward[0] * -32;
155  org[1] = ent->client->ps.origin[1] + flatforward[1] * -32;
156  //org[2] = ent->client->ps.origin[2] + 12; // 12 units to play with
157  org[2] = ent->client->ps.origin[2] + 24.f; // 12 units to play with
158 
159  //VectorSet( point, org[0], org[1], org[2] - 9.6f - 24.f ); // diff between playerlegsMins and playerlegsMaxs z + 24 units to play with
160  VectorSet(point, org[0], org[1], org[2] - (24.f - 2.4f) - 24.f); // diff between playerlegsMins and playerlegsMaxs z + 24 units to play with
161 
162  trap_TraceCapsule(&tr, org, playerlegsProneMins, playerlegsProneMaxs, point, ent->s.number, mask);
163 
164  if (!tr.startsolid || tr.entityNum < MAX_CLIENTS)
165  {
166  VectorCopy(tr.endpos, org);
167  //VectorSet( point, org[0], org[1], org[2] + 9.6f );
168  VectorSet(point, org[0], org[1], org[2] + (24.f - 2.4f));
169 
170  trap_TraceCapsule(&tr, org, playerlegsProneMins, playerlegsProneMaxs, point, ent->s.number, mask);
171 
172  if (tr.startsolid && tr.entityNum < MAX_CLIENTS)
173  {
174  tr.startsolid = qfalse;
175  }
176  }
177  }
178  }
179  else if (ent->s.eType == ET_CORPSE)
180  {
181  vec3_t pos;
182 
183  VectorCopy(ent->s.pos.trBase, pos);
184  pos[2] += 4; // move up a bit - corpses normally got their origin slightly in the ground
185  trap_Trace(&tr, pos, ent->r.mins, ent->r.maxs, pos, ent->s.number, mask);
186  // don't crush corpses against players
187  //if( tr.startsolid && g_entities[ tr.entityNum ].client )
188  // return NULL;
189  }
190  else if (ent->s.eType == ET_MISSILE)
191  {
192  trap_Trace(&tr, ent->s.pos.trBase, ent->r.mins, ent->r.maxs, ent->s.pos.trBase, ent->r.ownerNum, mask);
193  }
194  else
195  {
196  trap_Trace(&tr, ent->s.pos.trBase, ent->r.mins, ent->r.maxs, ent->s.pos.trBase, ent->s.number, mask);
197  }
198 
199  if (tr.startsolid)
200  {
201  return &g_entities[tr.entityNum];
202  }
203 
204  return NULL;
205 }

296 qboolean G_TryPushingEntity(gentity_t *check, gentity_t *pusher, vec3_t move, vec3_t amove)
297 {
298  vec3_t org, org2, move2;
299  gentity_t *block;
300  vec3_t matrix[3], transpose[3];
301 
302 #define JITTER_INC 4
303 #define JITTER_MAX (check->r.maxs[0] / 2.0f)
304 
305  // EF_MOVER_STOP will just stop when contacting another entity
306  // instead of pushing it, but entities can still ride on top of it
307  if ((pusher->s.eFlags & EF_MOVER_STOP) &&
308  check->s.groundEntityNum != pusher->s.number)
309  {
310  //pusher->s.eFlags |= EF_MOVER_BLOCKED;
311  return qfalse;
312  }
313 
314  // save off the old position
315  if (pushed_p > &pushed[MAX_GENTITIES])
316  {
317  G_Error("pushed_p > &pushed[MAX_GENTITIES]\n");
318  }
319  pushed_p->ent = check;
320  VectorCopy(check->s.pos.trBase, pushed_p->origin);
321  VectorCopy(check->s.apos.trBase, pushed_p->angles);
322  if (check->client)
323  {
324  pushed_p->deltayaw = check->client->ps.delta_angles[YAW];
325  VectorCopy(check->client->ps.origin, pushed_p->origin);
326  }
327  pushed_p++;
328 
329  // try moving the contacted entity
330  VectorAdd(check->s.pos.trBase, move, check->s.pos.trBase);
331  if (check->client)
332  {
333  // make sure the client's view rotates when on a rotating mover
334  // - this is done client-side now
335  // - only do this if player is prone or using set mortar - No! realism!
336  //if ((check->client->ps.eFlags & EF_PRONE) || GetWeaponTableData(check->s.weapon)->isMortarSet)
337  {
338  check->client->ps.delta_angles[YAW] += ANGLE2SHORT(amove[YAW]);
339  }
340  }
341 
342  // figure movement due to the pusher's amove
343  CreateRotationMatrix(amove, transpose);
344  TransposeMatrix(transpose, matrix);
345  if (check->client)
346  {
347  VectorSubtract(check->client->ps.origin, pusher->r.currentOrigin, org);
348  }
349  else
350  {
351  VectorSubtract(check->s.pos.trBase, pusher->r.currentOrigin, org);
352  }
353  VectorCopy(org, org2);
354  RotatePoint(org2, matrix);
355  VectorSubtract(org2, org, move2);
356  VectorAdd(check->s.pos.trBase, move2, check->s.pos.trBase);
357  if (check->client)
358  {
359  VectorAdd(check->client->ps.origin, move, check->client->ps.origin);
360  VectorAdd(check->client->ps.origin, move2, check->client->ps.origin);
361  }
362 
363  // may have pushed them off an edge
364  if (check->s.groundEntityNum != pusher->s.number)
365  {
366  check->s.groundEntityNum = -1;
367  }
368 
369  block = G_TestEntityPosition(check);
370  if (!block)
371  {
372  // pushed ok
373  if (check->client)
374  {
375  VectorCopy(check->client->ps.origin, check->r.currentOrigin);
376  }
377  else
378  {
379  VectorCopy(check->s.pos.trBase, check->r.currentOrigin);
380  }
381  return qtrue;
382  }
383 
384  // if blocking entity is a player, try to move this player first.
385 
386  if (block->client)
387  {
388  pushedStackDepth++;
389  if (pushedStackDepth < PUSH_STACK_DEPTH && G_TryPushingEntity(block, pusher, move, amove))
390  {
391  // pushed ok
392  if (check->client)
393  {
394  VectorCopy(check->client->ps.origin, check->r.currentOrigin);
395  }
396  else
397  {
398  VectorCopy(check->s.pos.trBase, check->r.currentOrigin);
399  }
400  return qtrue;
401  }
402  pushedStackDepth--;
403  }
404 
405  // if still not valid, move them around to see if we can find a good spot
406  if (JITTER_MAX > JITTER_INC)
407  {
408  float x, fx, y, fy, z, fz;
409 
410  VectorCopy(check->s.pos.trBase, org);
411  if (check->client)
412  {
413  VectorCopy(check->client->ps.origin, org);
414  }
415  for (z = 0; z < JITTER_MAX; z += JITTER_INC)
416  for (fz = -z; fz <= z; fz += 2 * z)
417  {
418  for (x = JITTER_INC; x < JITTER_MAX; x += JITTER_INC)
419  for (fx = -x; fx <= x; fx += 2 * x)
420  {
421  for (y = JITTER_INC; y < JITTER_MAX; y += JITTER_INC)
422  for (fy = -y; fy <= y; fy += 2 * y)
423  {
424  VectorSet(move2, fx, fy, fz);
425  VectorAdd(org, move2, org2);
426  VectorCopy(org2, check->s.pos.trBase);
427  if (check->client)
428  {
429  VectorCopy(org2, check->client->ps.origin);
430  }
431 
432  // do the test
433  block = G_TestEntityPosition(check);
434  if (!block)
435  {
436  // pushed ok
437  if (check->client)
438  {
439  VectorCopy(check->client->ps.origin, check->r.currentOrigin);
440  }
441  else
442  {
443  VectorCopy(check->s.pos.trBase, check->r.currentOrigin);
444  }
445  return qtrue;
446  }
447  }
448  }
449  if (fz == 0.f)
450  {
451  break;
452  }
453  }
454  // didnt work, so set the position back
455  VectorCopy(org, check->s.pos.trBase);
456  if (check->client)
457  {
458  VectorCopy(org, check->client->ps.origin);
459  }
460  }
461 
462  // if it is ok to leave in the old position, do it
463  // this is only relevent for riding entities, not pushed
464  // Sliding trapdoors can cause this.
465  VectorCopy((pushed_p - 1)->origin, check->s.pos.trBase);
466  if (check->client)
467  {
468  VectorCopy((pushed_p - 1)->origin, check->client->ps.origin);
469  }
470  VectorCopy((pushed_p - 1)->angles, check->s.apos.trBase);
471  block = G_TestEntityPosition(check);
472  if (!block)
473  {
474  check->s.groundEntityNum = -1;
475  pushed_p--;
476  return qtrue;
477  }
478 
479  // blocked
480  return qfalse;
481 }

498 qboolean G_MoverPush(gentity_t *pusher, vec3_t move, vec3_t amove, gentity_t **obstacle)
499 {
500  int i, e;
501  gentity_t *check;
502  vec3_t mins, maxs;
503  pushed_t *p;
504  pushed_t *work;
505  int entityList[MAX_GENTITIES];
506  int moveList[MAX_GENTITIES];
507  int listedEntities, moveEntities;
508  vec3_t totalMins, totalMaxs;
509 
510  *obstacle = NULL;
511 
512  // mins/maxs are the bounds at the destination
513  // totalMins / totalMaxs are the bounds for the entire move
514  if (pusher->r.currentAngles[0] != 0.f || pusher->r.currentAngles[1] != 0.f || pusher->r.currentAngles[2] != 0.f
515  || amove[0] != 0.f || amove[1] != 0.f || amove[2] != 0.f)
516  {
517  float radius;
518 
519  radius = RadiusFromBounds(pusher->r.mins, pusher->r.maxs);
520 
521  for (i = 0; i < 3; i++)
522  {
523  mins[i] = pusher->r.currentOrigin[i] - radius + move[i];
524  maxs[i] = pusher->r.currentOrigin[i] + radius + move[i];
525  totalMins[i] = pusher->r.currentOrigin[i] - radius;
526  totalMaxs[i] = pusher->r.currentOrigin[i] + radius;
527  }
528  }
529  else
530  {
531  for (i = 0; i < 3; i++)
532  {
533  mins[i] = pusher->r.absmin[i] + move[i];
534  maxs[i] = pusher->r.absmax[i] + move[i];
535  }
536 
537  VectorCopy(pusher->r.absmin, totalMins);
538  VectorCopy(pusher->r.absmax, totalMaxs);
539  }
540  for (i = 0; i < 3; i++)
541  {
542  if (move[i] > 0)
543  {
544  totalMaxs[i] += move[i];
545  }
546  else
547  {
548  totalMins[i] += move[i];
549  }
550  }
551 
552  // unlink the pusher so we don't get it in the entityList
553  trap_UnlinkEntity(pusher);
554 
555  listedEntities = trap_EntitiesInBox(totalMins, totalMaxs, entityList, MAX_GENTITIES);
556 
557  // move the pusher to it's final position
558  VectorAdd(pusher->r.currentOrigin, move, pusher->r.currentOrigin);
559  VectorAdd(pusher->r.currentAngles, amove, pusher->r.currentAngles);
560  trap_LinkEntity(pusher);
561 
562  moveEntities = 0;
563  // see if any solid entities are inside the final position
564  for (e = 0 ; e < listedEntities ; e++)
565  {
566  check = &g_entities[entityList[e]];
567 
568  if (check->s.eType == ET_ALARMBOX)
569  {
570  continue;
571  }
572 
573  if (check->isProp && check->s.eType == ET_PROP)
574  {
575  continue;
576  }
577 
578  // only push items and players
579  if (check->s.eType != ET_MISSILE && check->s.eType != ET_ITEM && check->s.eType != ET_PLAYER && !check->physicsObject)
580  {
581  continue;
582  }
583 
584  if (check->s.eType == ET_MISSILE && check->s.groundEntityNum != pusher->s.number)
585  {
586  if (check->methodOfDeath == MOD_LANDMINE)
587  {
588  if (check->s.effect1Time == 1)
589  {
590  LandMineTrigger(check);
591  }
592  }
593  continue;
594  }
595 
596  if (check->s.eType == ET_PLAYER && check->client && ((check->client->ps.eFlags & EF_TAGCONNECT) || (check->client->ps.pm_type == PM_NOCLIP)))
597  {
598  continue;
599  }
600 
601  //if ( check->s.eType == ET_MISSILE && VectorLengthSquared( check->s.pos.trDelta ) ) {
602  // continue; // it's moving
603  //}
604 
605  // if the entity is standing on the pusher, it will definitely be moved
606  if (check->s.groundEntityNum != pusher->s.number)
607  {
608  // see if the ent needs to be tested
609  if (check->r.absmin[0] >= maxs[0]
610  || check->r.absmin[1] >= maxs[1]
611  || check->r.absmin[2] >= maxs[2]
612  || check->r.absmax[0] <= mins[0]
613  || check->r.absmax[1] <= mins[1]
614  || check->r.absmax[2] <= mins[2])
615  {
616  continue;
617  }
618  // see if the ent's bbox is inside the pusher's final position
619  // this does allow a fast moving object to pass through a thin entity...
620  if (G_TestEntityPosition(check) != pusher)
621  {
622  continue;
623  }
624  }
625 
626  moveList[moveEntities++] = entityList[e];
627  }
628 
629  // unlink all to be moved entities so they cannot get stuck in each other
630  for (e = 0; e < moveEntities; e++)
631  {
632  check = &g_entities[moveList[e]];
633 
634  trap_UnlinkEntity(check);
635  }
636 
637  for (e = 0; e < moveEntities; e++)
638  {
639  check = &g_entities[moveList[e]];
640 
641  // some situations in front of mover should gib players (by damage)
642  switch (check->s.eType)
643  {
644  case ET_PLAYER:
645  if (!check->client)
646  {
647  break;
648  }
649 
650  if (check->s.groundEntityNum != pusher->s.number)
651  {
652  if (check->client->ps.eFlags & (EF_DEAD | EF_PRONE | EF_PRONE_MOVING))
653  {
654  trap_LinkEntity(check);
655  G_Damage(check, pusher, pusher, NULL, NULL, GIB_DAMAGE(check->health), 0, MOD_CRUSH);
656  moveList[e] = ENTITYNUM_NONE; // prevent re-linking later on
657  continue;
658  }
659  }
660  break;
661  case ET_CORPSE: // always gib corpses ...
662  trap_LinkEntity(check);
663  GibEntity(check, ENTITYNUM_WORLD);
664  moveList[e] = ENTITYNUM_NONE; // prevent re-linking later on
665  continue;
666  case ET_ITEM:
667  // items should be removed (except CTF objectives)
668  if (check->s.groundEntityNum == ENTITYNUM_WORLD)
669  {
670  if (check->item->giType != IT_TEAM)
671  {
672  trap_LinkEntity(check);
673  G_FreeEntity(check);
674  moveList[e] = ENTITYNUM_NONE;
675  continue;
676  }
677  }
678  break;
679  default:
680  break;
681  }
682  // the entity needs to be pushed
683  pushedStackDepth = 0; // new push, reset stack depth
684  if (G_TryPushingEntity(check, pusher, move, amove))
685  {
686 
687  // link it in now so nothing else tries to clip into us
688  trap_LinkEntity(check);
689  continue;
690  }
691 
692  // the move was blocked an entity
693 
694  // bobbing entities are instant-kill and never get blocked
695  if (pusher->s.pos.trType == TR_SINE || pusher->s.apos.trType == TR_SINE)
696  {
697  G_Damage(check, pusher, pusher, NULL, NULL, check->client ? GIB_DAMAGE(check->health) : GIB_ENT, 0, MOD_CRUSH);
698  continue;
699  }
700 
701 
702  // save off the obstacle so we can call the block function (crush, etc)
703  *obstacle = check;
704 
705  // move back any entities we already moved
706  // go backwards, so if the same entity was pushed
707  // twice, it goes back to the original position
708  // changed the loop slightly to avoid checking an invalid
709  // pointer (do the -1 inside the loop, > instead of >=)
710  for (p = pushed_p ; p > pushed ; p--)
711  {
712  work = p - 1;
713 
714  VectorCopy(work->origin, work->ent->s.pos.trBase);
715  VectorCopy(work->angles, work->ent->s.apos.trBase);
716  if (work->ent->client)
717  {
718  work->ent->client->ps.delta_angles[YAW] = work->deltayaw;
719  VectorCopy(work->origin, work->ent->client->ps.origin);
720  }
721  }
722 
723  // link all entities at their original position
724  for (e = 0; e < moveEntities; e++)
725  {
726  check = &g_entities[moveList[e]];
727 
728  trap_LinkEntity(check);
729  }
730  // movement failed
731  return qfalse;
732  }
733  // link all entities at their final position
734  for (e = 0; e < moveEntities; e++)
735  {
736  check = &g_entities[moveList[e]];
737 
738  trap_LinkEntity(check);
739  }
740  // movement was successfull
741  return qtrue;
742 }

748 void G_MoverTeam(gentity_t *ent)
749 {
750  vec3_t move, amove;
751  gentity_t *part, *obstacle;
752  vec3_t origin, angles;
753 
754  obstacle = NULL;
755 
756  // make sure all team slaves can move before commiting
757  // any moves or calling any think functions
758  // if the move is blocked, all moved objects will be backed out
759  pushed_p = pushed;
760  for (part = ent ; part ; part = part->teamchain)
761  {
762  // get current position
763  BG_EvaluateTrajectory(&part->s.pos, level.time, origin, qfalse, ent->s.effect2Time);
764  BG_EvaluateTrajectory(&part->s.apos, level.time, angles, qtrue, ent->s.effect2Time);
765  VectorSubtract(origin, part->r.currentOrigin, move);
766  VectorSubtract(angles, part->r.currentAngles, amove);
767 
768  if (part->s.eFlags == EF_MOVER_STOP)
769  {
770  part->s.eFlags &= ~EF_MOVER_BLOCKED;
771  }
772 
773  if (!G_MoverPush(part, move, amove, &obstacle))
774  {
775  break; // move was blocked
776  }
777  }
778 
779  if (part)
780  {
781  // go back to the previous position
782  for (part = ent ; part ; part = part->teamchain)
783  {
784  part->s.pos.trTime += level.time - level.previousTime;
785  part->s.apos.trTime += level.time - level.previousTime;
786  BG_EvaluateTrajectory(&part->s.pos, level.time, part->r.currentOrigin, qfalse, ent->s.effect2Time);
787  BG_EvaluateTrajectory(&part->s.apos, level.time, part->r.currentAngles, qtrue, ent->s.effect2Time);
788  trap_LinkEntity(part);
789  }
790 
791  // if the pusher has a "blocked" function, call it
792  if (ent->blocked)
793  {
794  ent->blocked(ent, obstacle);
795  }
796  return;
797  }
798 
799  // the move succeeded
800  for (part = ent ; part ; part = part->teamchain)
801  {
802  // call the reached function if time is at or past end point
803 
804  // opening/closing sliding door
805  if (part->s.pos.trType == TR_LINEAR_STOP)
806  {
807  if (level.time >= part->s.pos.trTime + part->s.pos.trDuration)
808  {
809  if (part->reached)
810  {
811  part->reached(part);
812  }
813  }
814  }
815  // opening or closing rotating door
816  else if (part->s.apos.trType == TR_LINEAR_STOP)
817  {
818  if (level.time >= part->s.apos.trTime + part->s.apos.trDuration)
819  {
820  if (part->reached)
821  {
822  part->reached(part);
823  }
824  }
825  }
826  }
827 }

880 void SetMoverState(gentity_t *ent, moverState_t moverState, int time)
881 {
882  vec3_t delta;
883  float f;
884  qboolean kicked = (qboolean)(ent->flags & FL_KICKACTIVATE);
885  qboolean soft = (qboolean)(ent->flags & FL_SOFTACTIVATE);
886 
887  ent->moverState = moverState;
888  ent->s.pos.trTime = time;
889  ent->s.apos.trTime = time;
890  switch (moverState)
891  {
892  case MOVER_POS1:
893  VectorCopy(ent->pos1, ent->s.pos.trBase);
894  ent->s.pos.trType = TR_STATIONARY;
895  ent->active = qfalse;
896  break;
897  case MOVER_POS2:
898  VectorCopy(ent->pos2, ent->s.pos.trBase);
899  ent->s.pos.trType = TR_STATIONARY;
900  break;
901 
902  case MOVER_POS3:
903  VectorCopy(ent->pos3, ent->s.pos.trBase);
904  ent->s.pos.trType = TR_STATIONARY;
905  break;
906 
907  case MOVER_2TO3:
908  VectorCopy(ent->pos2, ent->s.pos.trBase);
909  VectorSubtract(ent->pos3, ent->pos2, delta);
910  f = 1000.0f / ent->s.pos.trDuration;
911  VectorScale(delta, f, ent->s.pos.trDelta);
912  ent->s.pos.trType = TR_LINEAR_STOP;
913  break;
914  case MOVER_3TO2:
915  VectorCopy(ent->pos3, ent->s.pos.trBase);
916  VectorSubtract(ent->pos2, ent->pos3, delta);
917  f = 1000.0f / ent->s.pos.trDuration;
918  VectorScale(delta, f, ent->s.pos.trDelta);
919  ent->s.pos.trType = TR_LINEAR_STOP;
920  break;
921 
922  case MOVER_1TO2: // opening
923  VectorCopy(ent->pos1, ent->s.pos.trBase);
924  VectorSubtract(ent->pos2, ent->pos1, delta);
925  // numerous changes start here
926  ent->s.pos.trDuration = ent->gDuration;
927  f = 1000.0f / ent->s.pos.trDuration;
928  VectorScale(delta, f, ent->s.pos.trDelta);
929  ent->s.pos.trType = TR_LINEAR_STOP;
930 #ifdef FEATURE_OMNIBOT
931  {
932  const char *pName = _GetEntityName(ent);
933 
934  if (Q_stricmp(pName, ""))
935  {
936  Bot_Util_SendTrigger(ent, NULL, va("%s_Moving", pName), "opening");
937  }
938  }
939 #endif
940  break;
941  case MOVER_2TO1: // closing
942  VectorCopy(ent->pos2, ent->s.pos.trBase);
943  VectorSubtract(ent->pos1, ent->pos2, delta);
944  if (ent->closespeed != 0.f) // handle doors with different close speeds
945  {
946  ent->s.pos.trDuration = ent->gDurationBack;
947  f = 1000.0f / ent->gDurationBack;
948  }
949  else
950  {
951  ent->s.pos.trDuration = ent->gDuration;
952  f = 1000.0f / ent->s.pos.trDuration;
953  }
954  VectorScale(delta, f, ent->s.pos.trDelta);
955  ent->s.pos.trType = TR_LINEAR_STOP;
956 #ifdef FEATURE_OMNIBOT
957  {
958  const char *pName = _GetEntityName(ent);
959 
960  if (Q_stricmp(pName, ""))
961  {
962  Bot_Util_SendTrigger(ent, NULL, va("%s_Moving", pName), "closing");
963  }
964  }
965 #endif
966  break;
967 
968  case MOVER_POS1ROTATE: // at close
969  VectorCopy(ent->r.currentAngles, ent->s.apos.trBase);
970  ent->s.apos.trType = TR_STATIONARY;
971 #ifdef FEATURE_OMNIBOT
972  {
973  const char *pName = _GetEntityName(ent);
974 
975  if (Q_stricmp(pName, ""))
976  {
977  Bot_Util_SendTrigger(ent, NULL, va("%s_Moving", pName), "closed");
978  }
979  }
980 #endif
981  break;
982  case MOVER_POS2ROTATE: // at open
983  VectorCopy(ent->r.currentAngles, ent->s.apos.trBase);
984  ent->s.apos.trType = TR_STATIONARY;
985 #ifdef FEATURE_OMNIBOT
986  {
987  const char *pName = _GetEntityName(ent);
988 
989  if (Q_stricmp(pName, ""))
990  {
991  Bot_Util_SendTrigger(ent, NULL, va("%s_Moving", pName), "opened");
992  }
993  }
994 #endif
995  break;
996  case MOVER_1TO2ROTATE: // opening
997  VectorClear(ent->s.apos.trBase); // set base to start position {0,0,0}
998 
999  if (kicked)
1000  {
1001  f = 2000.0f / ent->gDuration; // double speed when kicked open
1002  ent->s.apos.trDuration = ent->gDuration / 2.0f;
1003  }
1004  else if (soft)
1005  {
1006  f = 500.0f / ent->gDuration; // 1/2 speed when soft opened
1007  ent->s.apos.trDuration = ent->gDuration * 2;
1008  }
1009  else
1010  {
1011  f = 1000.0f / ent->gDuration;
1012  //ent->s.apos.trDuration = ent->gDurationBack; // durationback?
1013  ent->s.apos.trDuration = ent->gDuration;
1014  }
1015  VectorScale(ent->rotate, f * ent->angle, ent->s.apos.trDelta);
1016  ent->s.apos.trType = TR_LINEAR_STOP;
1017  break;
1018  case MOVER_2TO1ROTATE: // closing
1019  VectorScale(ent->rotate, ent->angle, ent->s.apos.trBase); // set base to end position
1020  // (kicked closes same as normally opened)
1021  // (soft closes at 1/2 speed)
1022  f = 1000.0f / ent->gDuration;
1023  ent->s.apos.trDuration = ent->gDuration;
1024  if (soft)
1025  {
1026  ent->s.apos.trDuration *= 2;
1027  f *= 0.5f;
1028  }
1029  VectorScale(ent->s.apos.trBase, -f, ent->s.apos.trDelta);
1030  ent->s.apos.trType = TR_LINEAR_STOP;
1031  ent->active = qfalse;
1032  break;
1033  }
1034  BG_EvaluateTrajectory(&ent->s.pos, level.time, ent->r.currentOrigin, qfalse, ent->s.effect2Time);
1035  //if (!(ent->r.svFlags & SVF_NOCLIENT) || (ent->r.contents)) // added this for bats, but this is safe for all movers, since if they aren't solid, and aren't visible to the client, they don't need to be linked
1036  // trap_LinkEntity( ent );
1037 }

1300 qboolean IsBinaryMoverBlocked(gentity_t *ent, gentity_t *other, gentity_t *activator)
1301 {
1302  if (Q_stricmp(ent->classname, "func_door_rotating") == 0)
1303  {
1304  vec3_t angles;
1305  vec3_t dir;
1306  vec3_t pos;
1307  vec3_t vec;
1308  vec3_t forward;
1309  qboolean is_relay = qfalse;
1310  float dot;
1311 
1312  if (ent->spawnflags & DOOR_ROTATING_FORCE)
1313  {
1314  return qfalse;
1315  }
1316 
1317  // only check for blockage by players
1318  if (!activator)
1319  {
1320  if (other && Q_stricmp(other->classname, "target_relay") == 0)
1321  {
1322  is_relay = qtrue;
1323  }
1324  else /*if(!activator->client) */
1325  {
1326  return qfalse;
1327  }
1328  }
1329 
1330  VectorAdd(ent->r.absmin, ent->r.absmax, pos);
1331  VectorScale(pos, 0.5f, pos);
1332 
1333  VectorSubtract(pos, ent->s.origin, dir);
1334  vectoangles(dir, angles);
1335 
1336  if (ent->rotate[YAW] != 0.f)
1337  {
1338  angles[YAW] += ent->angle;
1339  }
1340  else if (ent->rotate[PITCH] != 0.f)
1341  {
1342  angles[PITCH] += ent->angle;
1343  }
1344  else if (ent->rotate[ROLL] != 0.f)
1345  {
1346  angles[ROLL] += ent->angle;
1347  }
1348 
1349  AngleVectors(angles, forward, NULL, NULL);
1350  // VectorSubtract (other->r.currentOrigin, pos, vec);
1351 
1352  if (is_relay)
1353  {
1354  VectorSubtract(other->r.currentOrigin, pos, vec);
1355  }
1356  else
1357  {
1358  VectorSubtract(activator->r.currentOrigin, pos, vec);
1359  }
1360 
1361  VectorNormalize(vec);
1362  dot = DotProduct(vec, forward);
1363 
1364  if (dot >= 0)
1365  {
1366  return qtrue;
1367  }
1368  else
1369  {
1370  return qfalse;
1371  }
1372  }
1373 
1374  return qfalse;
1375 }

1823 void InitMover(gentity_t *ent)
1824 {
1825  vec3_t move;
1826  float distance;
1827 
1828  // if the "model2" key is set, use a seperate model
1829  // for drawing, but clip against the brushes
1830  if (ent->model2)
1831  {
1832  ent->s.modelindex2 = G_ModelIndex(ent->model2);
1833  }
1834 
1835  if (!Q_stricmp(ent->classname, "func_secret"))
1836  {
1837  ent->use = Use_TrinaryMover;
1838  ent->reached = Reached_TrinaryMover;
1839  }
1840  else if (!Q_stricmp(ent->classname, "func_rotating"))
1841  {
1842  ent->use = Use_Func_Rotate;
1843  ent->reached = NULL; // rotating can never reach
1844  }
1845  else
1846  {
1847  ent->use = Use_BinaryMover;
1848  ent->reached = Reached_BinaryMover;
1849  }
1850 
1851  ent->moverState = MOVER_POS1;
1852  ent->r.svFlags &= SVF_IGNOREBMODELEXTENTS;
1853  ent->s.eType = ET_MOVER;
1854 
1855  VectorCopy(ent->pos1, ent->r.currentOrigin);
1856  trap_LinkEntity(ent);
1857 
1858  ent->s.pos.trType = TR_STATIONARY;
1859  VectorCopy(ent->pos1, ent->s.pos.trBase);
1860 
1861  // calculate time to reach second position from speed
1862  VectorSubtract(ent->pos2, ent->pos1, move);
1863  distance = VectorLength(move);
1864  if (ent->speed == 0.f)
1865  {
1866  ent->speed = 100;
1867  }
1868 
1869  // open time based on speed
1870  VectorScale(move, ent->speed, ent->gDelta);
1871  ent->s.pos.trDuration = (int)(distance * 1000.f / ent->speed);
1872  if (ent->s.pos.trDuration <= 0)
1873  {
1874  ent->s.pos.trDuration = 1;
1875  }
1876  ent->gDurationBack = ent->gDuration = ent->s.pos.trDuration;
1877 
1878  // close time based on speed
1879  if (ent->closespeed != 0.f)
1880  {
1881  VectorScale(move, ent->closespeed, ent->gDelta);
1882  ent->gDurationBack = (int)(distance * 1000.f / ent->closespeed);
1883  if (ent->gDurationBack <= 0)
1884  {
1885  ent->gDurationBack = 1;
1886  }
1887  }
1888 }

2045 static void Touch_DoorTriggerSpectator(gentity_t *ent, gentity_t *other, trace_t *trace)
2046 {

2049

2052  Q_fabs((other->s.origin[axis] - ent->r.absmin[axis])))
2053  {

2063  {

2066  continue;

2068  origin[i] = (ent->r.absmin[i] + ent->r.absmax[i]) * 0.5f;
2069  }
2070  vectoangles(dir, angles);
2071  TeleportPlayer(other, origin, angles);

2155 void Think_SpawnNewDoorTrigger(gentity_t *ent)
2156 {
2157  gentity_t *other;
2158  vec3_t mins, maxs;
2159  int i, best = 0;
2160 
2161  // set all of the slaves as shootable
2162  for (other = ent ; other ; other = other->teamchain)
2163  {
2164  other->takedamage = qtrue;
2165  }
2166 
2167  // find the bounds of everything on the team
2168  VectorCopy(ent->r.absmin, mins);
2169  VectorCopy(ent->r.absmax, maxs);
2170 
2171  for (other = ent->teamchain ; other ; other = other->teamchain)
2172  {
2173  AddPointToBounds(other->r.absmin, mins, maxs);
2174  AddPointToBounds(other->r.absmax, mins, maxs);
2175  }
2176 
2177  // find the thinnest axis, which will be the one we expand
2178  for (i = 1 ; i < 3 ; i++)
2179  {
2180  if (maxs[i] - mins[i] < maxs[best] - mins[best])
2181  {
2182  best = i;
2183  }
2184  }
2185  maxs[best] += 120;
2186  mins[best] -= 120;
2187 
2188  // create a trigger with this size
2189  other = G_Spawn();
2190  VectorCopy(mins, other->r.mins);
2191  VectorCopy(maxs, other->r.maxs);
2192  other->parent = ent;
2193  other->r.contents = CONTENTS_TRIGGER;
2194  other->touch = Touch_DoorTrigger;
2195  trap_LinkEntity(other);
2196 
2197  MatchTeam(ent, ent->moverState, level.time);
2198 }

2962 void Reached_Train(gentity_t *ent)
2963 {

2967  float length;
2968

2970  {

2972  }

2975  {
2976  return;
2977  }
2978 
2979  // fire all other targets
2980  G_UseTargets(next, NULL);
2981 
2982  // set the new trajectory

2995  {
2996  speed = next->speed * g_moverScale.value;
2997  }
2998  else
2999  {
3000  // otherwise use the train's speed
3001  speed = ent->speed;
3002  }
3003  if (speed < 1)
3004  {
3005  speed = 1;
3006  }
3007

3009  length = VectorDistance(ent->pos2, ent->pos1);
3010

4325 void func_explosive_explode(gentity_t *self, gentity_t *inflictor, gentity_t *attacker, int damage, meansOfDeath_t mod)
4326 {

4329  vec3_t dir = { 0, 0, 1 };
4330  gentity_t *tent = &g_entities[MAX_CLIENTS - 1];
4331  int hash;
4332 
4333  self->takedamage = qfalse; // don't allow anything try to hurt me now that i'm exploding
4334

4336  self->nextthink = level.time + FRAMETIME;
4337 
4338  VectorSubtract(self->r.absmax, self->r.absmin, size);
4339  VectorScale(size, 0.5f, size);
4340  VectorAdd(self->r.absmin, size, origin);
4341 
4342  VectorCopy(origin, self->s.pos.trBase);

4344  G_UseTargets(self, attacker);
4345

4348  self->s.frame = self->key; // pass the type to the client ("glass", "wood", "metal", "gibs", "brick", "stone", "fabric", 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6)
4349 
4350  if (self->damage)
4351  {

4353  }
4354 
4355  // find target, aim at that
4356  if (self->target)
4357  {
4358  // FIXME: use self->targetnamehash one day ...
4359  hash = BG_StringHashValue(self->target);
4360 
4361  // since the explosive might need to fire the target rather than
4362  // aim at it, only aim at 'info_notnull' ents

4364  {

4366  if (!tent)
4367  {
4368  break;
4369  }
4370 
4371  if (!Q_stricmp(tent->classname, "info_notnull"))
4372  {
4373  break; // found an info_notnull
4374  }
4375  }
4376 
4377  if (tent)
4378  {
4379  VectorSubtract(tent->s.pos.trBase, self->s.pos.trBase, dir);
4380  VectorNormalize(dir);
4381  }
4382  }
4383 
4384  // if a valid target entity was not found, check for a specified 'angle' for the explosion direction
4385  if (!tent)
4386  {
4387  if (self->s.angles[1] != 0.f)
4388  {
4389  // up
4390  if (self->s.angles[1] == -1.f)
4391  {
4392  // it's 'up' by default
4393  }
4394  // down
4395  else if (self->s.angles[1] == -2.f)
4396  {
4397  dir[2] = -1;
4398  }
4399  // yawed
4400  else
4401  {
4402  RotatePointAroundVector(dir, dir, tv(1, 0, 0), self->s.angles[1]);
4403  }
4404  }
4405  }
4406 
4407  G_AddEvent(self, EV_EXPLODE, DirToByte(dir));
4408 
4409 #ifdef FEATURE_OMNIBOT
4410  // Omnibot trigger support

4412  {
4413  G_Script_ScriptEvent(self, "exploded", "");
4414  }
4415 #endif

4420  G_AddKillSkillPointsForDestruction(attacker, mod, &self->constructibleStats);
